Rich —

I don’t know the story, but if you ever decide to try researching further, this info from the finder’s guide to the BPL Dwiggins Collection might help give you a head start.

The relevant material is in Box #72.  
United States Postage Stamp Project:  
folder 24 — correspondence;  
ff. 25-26 — drawings & sketches;  
f. 27 — postal cards with sketches (annotated);  
ff. 28-29 — photographs of design by other artists;  
f. 30 — memos & clippings regarding project;  
ff. 31-34 — reference materials.

BTW, folders just after this in the same box are related to the currency project.

— Kent.
